The paper deals with the impact of jamming attacks on wireless communication systems, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also presents countermeasures for mitigating the effects of jamming attacks, which can be categorized under the sub-domain of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper considers the multiple-input single-output (MISO) broadcast channel, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
